            //- p.
            //-     The form of the light is a critical issue. Many existing box or rice paper lamps contain one or more halogen bulbs inside. Once on, these visually disrupt the forms and decouple them from the function of the light. The boxes become a cage that entomb a light point creating a nested hierarchy of forms. You cannot look at or appreciate the form without your eye being drawn to the bulb within. LED strips are both more environmentally friendly and break the restriction of circular enclosures for homogeneous light. The result is no longer a paper cage for a light, like a firefly in a jar, but a box whose essence is bright.
